Graph Questions ke MAIN TYPES (Patterns)
🟢 1. Traversal Problems (BFS / DFS)

👉 Sirf graph ko explore karna

Examples:

Number of Islands
Connected Components
Flood Fill

👉 Use:

DFS (deep jaana ho)
BFS (level-wise)
🔵 2. Shortest Path Problems

👉 Source se destination tak minimum distance

Types:

Unweighted → BFS
Weighted → Dijkstra
Negative weights → Bellman-Ford

Examples:

Shortest path in binary matrix
Network delay time
🟡 3. Cycle Detection

👉 Graph me loop hai ya nahi?

Types:

Undirected → DFS (parent check)
Directed → DFS (recursion stack)

Examples:

Detect cycle in graph
Course Schedule (cycle check)
🟣 4. Topological Sort (DAG)

👉 Dependencies wale questions

Use when:

“pehle yeh karo, fir yeh”

Examples:

Course Schedule
Task scheduling
🟠 5. Connected Components / Provinces

👉 Kitne groups hain graph me

Examples:

Number of Provinces
Friend Circles
🔴 6. Grid Based Graph (2D Matrix)

👉 Hidden graph 😏

Examples:

Number of Islands
Rotten Oranges
Shortest path in grid

👉 Mostly DFS / BFS

⚫ 7. Bipartite Graph

👉 Graph ko 2 groups me divide kar sakte ho?

Examples:

Check bipartite
Possible bipartition

👉 BFS / DFS + coloring

⚡ 8. Minimum Spanning Tree (MST)

👉 Minimum cost me graph connect karo

Algorithms:

Kruskal
Prim
🔥 9. Advanced (High Level)

👉 Thoda tough / Amazon level

Union-Find (DSU)
Bridges & Articulation Points
Strongly Connected Components (Kosaraju)
Floyd Warshall
